				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Games do <em>not</em> run from $8000; they run from whatever address appears in $FFFC-$FFFD. "JMP to program start" would involve loading  the following trampoline into RAM, loading A with the latch value, and then jumping to the trampoline:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; sei<br />&nbsp; sta latchAddr<br />&nbsp; ldx #$FD<br />&nbsp; txs&nbsp; ; normal power-on state of stack pointer<br />&nbsp; jmp &#40;$FFFC&#41;&nbsp; ; 6502 reset vector<br /></div>
<br />Some more buggy games may require that most of RAM be cleared to $FF values, so load this trampoline into upper stack space ($01C0-$01FF).
<br />
<br />And would your menu cart use the first cart's lockout chip? And how would you (cleanly) make the latch disappear from the bus as soon as it is written to once?</div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">tepples</a> on Wed Mar 01, 2006 6:30 am, edited 1 time in total.</span>
