				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I had an idea for something like this a while back, just imagining though.  I don't know how much the connectors would cost, probably too much since it's a custom type.  Then I figure a lot of bus driver chips.
<br />
<br />Maybe I'm just crazy, but I'd want the thing fully powered (externally) and possibly under control so the program could select any cart whenever it wants.  That'd be a hell of a hardware expansion usable by whatever fits in the NES's internal 2kB of RAM (well, depending on what carts are connected anyways, getting to be like a PC with infinite hardware configs).
<br />
<br />Also, with just cutting off the power of a cart to disable it (or just ICs in general), is that safe to do electrically?  I was wondering about that for some other designs.  Since the inputs would be getting voltage while VCC and GND are both 0V, a lot of chips will say things like max VCC+0.6V.  It makes the voltage difference sound unsafe, but I don't know.</div>

