					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">teaguecl wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You could try replacing all those chips with a programmable logic device.</div><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But how many pins would it need?</div>
<br />
<br />two 16bit address busses + two 8bit data busses = 48 lines.
<br />
<br />So double that and we get 96 total just for bridging all the I/O.  This application will need another dozen or so for good measure...  So we're looking at a 100+pin chip of some kind.
<br />
<br />Edit: Apparently, I can't add. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /></div>

